# Source file encoding (Windows)

All text sources in this repository must be **UTF-8 with LF** line endings. On Windows,
Cursor editor **Write** and **StrReplace** can silently save **UTF-16**, which breaks
`deno fmt` (files collapse to a single line) and fails CI (`deno task encoding:check`).

## Required workflow on Windows

After editing text sources with Write or StrReplace, run this before `deno fmt`:

```powershell
deno task encoding:check
```

If the check fails:

```powershell
deno task encoding:fix
deno fmt
```

Do not run `deno fmt` on UTF-16 files; it corrupts them further.

## When creating new files

Prefer shell writes with explicit UTF-8:

```powershell
$content = "export const example = 1;`n"
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText("$PWD\src\example.ts", $content, [System.Text.UTF8Encoding]::new($false))
```

Or use Deno:

```powershell
deno eval "await Deno.writeTextFile('src/example.ts', 'export const example = 1;\n')"
```